{"number":33,"verseCount":23,"verses":[[1,["And the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," said unto Moses, ",["Depart",["study-note-ref","a",[["Deut. 10:11","ot/deut/10.11"],"."]]],", ",["and",["clarity-word"]]," go up hence, thou and the people which thou hast brought up out of the land of Egypt, unto the land which I sware unto Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, saying, Unto thy ",["seed",["study-note-ref","b",[["Gen. 12:7","ot/gen/12.7"],"; ",["Abr. 2:6 (3–6, 19)","pgp/abr/2.6"],". ",["TG Seed of Abraham","tg/seed-of-abraham"],"."]]]," will I give it:"]],[2,["And I will send an ",["angel",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Angels","tg/angels"],"."]]]," before thee; and I will drive out the ",["Canaanite",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ex. 3:17 (8, 17)","ot/ex/3.17"],"; ",["13:5","ot/ex/13.5"],"."]]],", the Amorite, and the Hittite, and the Perizzite, the Hivite, and the Jebusite:"]],[3,["Unto a land ",["flowing",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 13:5","ot/ex/13.5"],"."]]]," with milk and honey: for I will not go up in the midst of thee; for thou ",["art",["clarity-word"]]," a stiffnecked people: lest I consume thee in the way."]],[4,[["¶ ",["para-mark"]],"And when the people heard these evil tidings, they ",["mourned",["study-note-ref","a",[["Num. 14:39","ot/num/14.39"],"."]]],": and no man did put on him his ",["ornaments",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ezek. 24:17 (17, 23)","ot/ezek/24.17"],"."]]],"."]],[5,["For the ",[["Lord",["small-caps"]],["deity-name"]]," had said unto Moses, Say unto the children of Israel, Ye ",["are",["clarity-word"]]," a ",["stiffnecked",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Stiffnecked","tg/stiffnecked"],"."]]]," people: ",["I",["study-note-ref","b",["OR if I came up … I would consume …"]]]," will come up into the midst of thee in a moment, and consume thee: therefore now put off thy ornaments from thee, that I may know what to do unto thee."]],[6,["And the children of Israel stripped themselves of their ornaments by the mount Horeb."]],[7,["And Moses took the ta